cyclone.name: PAINE
cyclone.current_location: about 285 miles WSW of Cabo San Lázaro, Mexico and 295 miles SSW of Punta Eugenia, Mexico
cyclone.trajectory: turning north then north-northeast and approaching the northwest coast of the Baja California Peninsula while remaining well south of Southern California
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: near or just south-east of Punta Eugenia, Baja California Peninsula

weather_observation.watch_coast: No U.S. coastal watches issued; Mexican government has not issued a watch—only warnings.
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical Storm Warning from Punta Eugenia to Cabo San Quintin, Baja California
weather_observation.impacted_coast: north-west Baja California Peninsula; moisture plume spreading into Southern California, Arizona and the Southwest U.S.
weather_observation.wind: Occasional gusty easterly to southeasterly winds, generally below tropical-storm force (<39 mph)
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected along the San Diego coast
weather_observation.rainfall: Moisture associated with Paine could bring 0.5–2 inches of rain to the San Diego region, locally higher over coastal foothills Tuesday night into Wednesday
weather_observation.other_hazards: Elevated surf and dangerous rip currents along Southern California beaches during mid-week
